.TH pif-publish 1  "pif-publish " 
.SH NAME
pif\-publish \- Publish an extension to the pif index
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBpif\-publish\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIDIRECTORY\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Publish an extension to the pif index
.PP
Prepares a contribution for the upstream registry. Reads release metadata from release.yaml in DIRECTORY (defaults to the current directory), validates it against the registry schema, and opens the draft pull\-request workflow.
.PP
You need a fork of the registry repository and GitHub credentials configured before running this command.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] [default: .]
Path to the extension directory (default: current directory)

The directory must contain a valid release.yaml describing the extension. pif validates the file against the registry schema before opening the contribution workflow.
